You'd do best by sanding the fiberglass filler (yuck) below the finish
level of the metal, and level the "caved and paved' area even with bondo
(phooey)

The only reason for this is the hairs of the glass reinforced material
may not lay down flush, and be noticable after you finished this
"repair" off.

